'''Charlene Newcomb''' is the author of several short stories for the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]s'', many of which were also available on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Hyperspace'']]: ''[[Fiction]]''. Her primary protagonist is [[Alexandra Winger|Alex Winger]].

==Biography==
Charlene Newcomb was born in [[Wikipedia:Spartanburg, South Carolina|Spartanburg, South Carolina]], and currently lives in [[Wikipedia:Manhattan, Kansas|Manhattan, Kansas]].

Newcomb graduated from [[Wikipedia:University of Maryland University College|University of Maryland, University College]] with a [[Wikipedia:Bachelor of Arts|B.A. degree]] in U.S. history after serving in the [[Wikipedia:United States Navy|United States Navy]]. She worked for the federal government in a civilian capacity for a short time before leaving [[Wikipedia:Maryland|Maryland]] for [[Wikipedia:North Carolina|North Carolina]] and then [[Wikipedia:Florida|Florida]]. She attended the [[Wikipedia:University of South Florida|University of South Florida]] and received a [[Wikipedia:Master's degree|master's degree]] in [[Wikipedia:library and information science|library and information science]] in [[1996]].

